A RESOLUTION
1 Commending the Archibald Bulloch Chapter of the National Society Daughters of the
2 American Revolution on its 61st anniversary; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia was founded by General James Edward Oglethorpe, who
4 received a royal charter to establish the 13th American colony in honor of King George II
5 and led 116 pioneers aboard the HMS Anne, landing near present-day Savannah on February
6 12, 1733; and
7 WHEREAS, since its founding 292 years ago, Georgia has grown from a settlement of early
8 colonists to a thriving state with an estimated population of 11 million, transitioning from a
9 predominantly rural economy to the commercial, financial, and cultural center of the
10 Southeast; and
11 WHEREAS, Bulloch County was established in 1796 as Georgia's 21st county, formed from
12 St. Philip's Parish and named in honor of Archibald Bulloch, a delegate to the Continental
13 Congress of 1775 and Georgia's first governor in 1776; and
14 WHEREAS, the Archibald Bulloch Chapter of the National Society Daughters of the
15 American Revolution was organized on February 29, 1964, with 17 charter members,
