19 Phillips Moore, Gerstle DeLoach Nevil, Marguerite Nunnally Neville, Edna DeLoach
20 Robbins, Patricia Mathewson Robbins, and Mary Groover Demmond Watson; and
21 WHEREAS, for more than six decades, the Archibald Bulloch Chapter has demonstrated
22 leadership at the local and state levels, contributed to national projects, and diligently worked
23 to uphold the objectives of historic preservation, education, and patriotism; and
24 WHEREAS, the chapter actively assists and encourages women in researching their
25 genealogy to identify patriots who served in the American Revolutionary War from April 19,
26 1775, to September 3, 1783, or who provided military service support; and
27 WHEREAS, under the leadership of Regent Martha Ann Tanner for the 2024-2026 term, the
28 Archibald Bulloch Chapter continues to promote awareness of Georgia's rich history and the
29 significance of the state's founding; and
30 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this distinguished organization be
31 appropriately honored.
32 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
33 the members of this body commend the Archibald Bulloch Chapter of the National Society
34 Daughters of the American Revolution upon the grand occasion of both its 61st anniversary
35 and this year's Georgia Day, which the chapter will celebrate on February 13, 2025, with an
36 open luncheon in Statesboro, Georgia.
